text: Great authentic Indian food. Was very skeptical of ordering Indian food as most of Indian restaurants serve tasteless Americanized version of Indian food but this restaurant delivered food to my hotel, on time with perfect amount of masala. Tried goat biryani and dal makhni. If you are Indian looking to revive Dhaba taste buds, look no further.

We went to buffet on Monday 11 am.
vegetable curry less choice and cold. tastes one day old curry. garlic naan not cooked properly. not recomending
Awesome food....  Good service...  One of the best Indian restaurants in Vegas... We had vegetarian food...  Tastes very good...

The food seems to be more like stale leftovers from yesterday.

All the curries were watery with a few vegetables or chicken /lamb pieces floating around somewhere in the mix .

The ambience inside the restaurant is fine, with Indian music playing away in the background.

If I ever come to this restaurant again , I will ensure I don't go for the buffet
I came here for lunch after reading the good reviews--it is outstanding!  Best Indian food I have eaten!

This place has just opened recently so we thought we would try it out and we were not disappointed! The food was on point, I was very happy with my lamb saag. We had great service and the owners were very nice and approachable. Will be back as soon as they get their alcohol license!

The owner is friendly. The establishment is spacious and well decorated. During our visit to Las Vegas we were craving some of our ethnic food and decided to give this place a try. Food was good, our biryani was a bit too spicy even though we requested a spice level of '2' it was redone for us. Dal was our favorite dish!
Great food and great service! Everything was made fresh to order and was amazing! Chili paneer was a great appetizer!
They have a pretty good buffet and reasonably priced. Some of the best Naan bread I've ever had. The owner and staff are very attentive and hospitable. If you haven't yet, Give it a try!

I'm new to Indian cuisine, and my boyfriend brought me to the lunch buffet. Feeling quite adventurous, I sampled nearly all of the dishes. The chicken tikka masala was amazing, as was everything else. The service was great and the atmosphere of the restaurant is very welcoming. The owner was very concerned with our visit and wanted to make sure we were enjoying ourselves. We will return.

Excellent. The owner greeted me at the door and invited me to try the buffet but I had a Groupon so I ordered from the menu. The Food is prepared fresh after ordering.  I ordered lamb chops and the vegetable Korma. Both excellent. I will be back to try the buffet

Great  lamb roganjosh. New Indian restaurant in a great location. Great food and service. The mango Lassi was sweet and delicious. Didn't get to try the dessert but they looked good. Recommend the lamb dishes.

I went to Jannat restaurant for dinner with my wife. I visited Vegas couple of times before and have tried lot of Indian restaurants but never found any good one. I searched on yelp and found about Jannat and after reading yelp reviews thought of trying it. 

The restaurant is a little off the strip but not too far away. 

At the restaurant, the server came and took our order. Then he brought us some roasted papad with mint and tamarind chutney. Although I am not a big fan of eating papad I still loved it since the chutney was amazing. The tamarind and mint chutney was thick and with perfect amount of liquid-ness. All the other Indian places I have tried, not only in Vegas but even in other cities, I have seen that the chutneys are merely full of water and too liquidy which takes away the whole taste. 

Anyways we ordered Aloo Tikki Chat (from appetizer), Dal Tadka & Malai Kofta (from entree), Aloo paratha, Onion kulcha, Butter naan. 

While we were waiting for the order, the owner of the restaurant Mr. Sunny came and greeted us and asked if we needed anything else and talked about this newly opened restaurant. He then went and asked the cook to make the entrees spice level as per our need. 

The aloo tikki chat was amazing, it was perfect mix of white chana (chole) and onions with the aloo tikki which is mix of aloo and other spices. The taste was literally as if we were eating at Delhi's road side street food. The dal tadka was very tasty and reminded me of the dhaba style tadka dal. I have seen at other Indian restaurants where the chef's put dry red chilli in tadka, that is not what I have seen in my native place or how we cook it. And this dal tadka was exactly how I expected which simple tadka of ghee with cumin seeds, onions and green chillis slightly saute and mixed with dal. Amazingly tasty.  

Malai kofta was very tasty as well. It was a perfect blend of sweetish gravy with the mix of spices on kofta. The kofta's are very soft and very tasty. My wife who doesn't like malai kofta much since the gravy is usually sweet and lot of Indian restaurants have it very sweet and it mostly feels like you are eating a sweet dish more than an entree. But this malai kofta at Jannat's restaurant was perfect mix of sweet and spiciness, that my wife loved it.   

Each entree comes with complementary basmati rice. The rice is not some ordinary rice that most of the Indian restaurants serve on the name of basmati rice, it is very tasty and a long grained rice.  

The aloo paratha and onion kulcha is a must try. The paratha is stuffed with lightly spiced potatoes which makes it very tasty that you wouldn't even want any pickle or raita with it. Even onion kulcha was amazing and stuffed with onions. Both were very soft enough to eat without the stuffing falling from them while eating. The butter naan was as usual soft and nice.  

People have mentioned that the restaurant is far from strip, but its actually not that far. Its hardly couple of miles which is very easier to drive if you have car or even get there by cab. The restaurant was cleaned and the owner and server are great. They make sure your personal food style like spice level and other things are taken care of. 

I loved this place and would definitely go there next time I am in Vegas. :)

This was my first time ever having Indian food, so I didn't have much to compare to. However, my in laws came with us and they've been to India and used to be friends with the owners of Shalimar (which used to be the best in town). They all agreed that this is the BEST Indian in town now.

We came because the yelp reviews were so high, but they really lived up to the hype. We had tandori chicken, tika masala, butter chicken and garlic and cheese naan. 

Everything was wonderful? Not too spicy. The rice was fluffy, the sauces were flavorful. Everyone was full and happy! We will definitely be back and bring our friends! Thank you!

Decided to give this place a second chance.. My husband and I went to Jannat last week. We were shocked cause the buffet table was "kinda" empty. Their food description says chicken tikka masala, but there's no chicken on it.. just sauce! Lol the saag paneer tastes so horrible! The lamb curry tastes weird and has this repulsive taste. I will never recommend this place nor come back here.

We had the lunch buffet and we really enjoy the different vegetable dishes.  Jannat has a different variety of vegetables dishes like okra and samosa chat which I normally don't see in other buffets. 

The restaurant is clean, with a romantic chalet theme. The service was excellent and I think we found this place will be our new favorite restaurant for Indian food.

Very good lunch buffet
Went for buffet lunch clean nice atmosphere and the food was delicious very pleasant took takeout for family love the white tablecloths and Indian coffee

Heads up, the second you enter, you will be enthusiastically greeted by Sunny, the owner. He's friendly and helpful and unnervingly good at the upsell- I spent significantly more than I'd planned without even thinking about it! But damn, he was right about that garlic naan...

For lunch, you have dine-in buffet or plate specials as your options- vegetarian plate is $10, non-veg is a buck more, both come with your choice of three courses (soup, app, entree), plus rice. I got one of each plate and basically made my own buffet at home, and there was more than enough food for three meals. Add on the naan, as the meals don't come with it, and a mango lassi for a special treat.

The soups weren't my thing- lentil was more brothy than usual and the tomato was on the boring side. The tandoori chicken app was a bit dry, but the chana samosa chaat was a flavorful favorite. The muttar paneer and the chicken tikka were both robust with great sauces, but neither came with the requested heat level. Overall, I enjoyed our meal but my guy thought it was pretty average. I might come back for the dine-in buffet, but their dinner prices a bit higher than I'd like to spend. I may have to come back for the lamb rogan josh though!

Props for having a nicely appointed interior- I am really hoping they do not utilize their patio seating to offer hookah, which became the focus of previous businesses in this location. Also, management should note that options available through their online ordering system are different from what is available on site- probably something to address to avoid an issue.

Best Indian food I have had in Las Vegas! Excellent and attentive service. My group all got the Paneer Tikka Masala, Chicken Korma, and Lamb Vindaloo, all were absolutely delicious (Chicken Korma is my new favorite!) Spice levels were perfect as well. I definitely recommend this spot!
My first Yelp review and this place was excellent! This was my first time eating Indian food and this place did not disappoint. I work right next door and I will make this place a staple
Really good food! The owner is a very nice man who walked us through the buffet and explained every dish. I very much recommend this place. I hope they succeed and will go back there soon. Enjoy!

Went to this place yesterday for buffet.Place was full which I always feel is the easiest way to gauge how popular the place is. They had a good number of vegetarian n meat dishes. Food was very tasty. My favorite was butter chicken and biryani. I have tried many Indian  buffets in Vegas ,which look like a mass production factory and every dish tastes d same. Well this was a total surprise for me.My son was actually licking his fingers n enjoying his food. Don't forget to try the gulabjamun and carrot pudding in the end. It was yum yum. I m definitely going there tonite and will take some pictures this time.
Last thing order Masala tea after your meal. I ordered one to go
They paid so much attention.. I was able to have a vegan meal and the food was so satisfying, fresh (they made it from scratch) and rich in flavor.. Very good!

I'm an indian buffet connoisseur and this place is one of the better buffets in town. A close after Gandhis and Paradise buffet. Came during Sunday lunch and my sister and I were the only ones there the entire time, but this place has only been open for only a month or so. The buffet does not have a lot of options, but it is $11 and what they do have is delicious. The butter chicken and lamb curry were amazing. The naan, tandoori chicken and curry chicken were also flavorful and good. They also had this mushroom curry which was delicious. The cheese in the chili paneer was dry and their veggie dishes werent that good. They had these potato like fritters that were great. Disappointed they didn't have saag paneer or chicken tikki masala. The mango lassi was good, but $4! It was warm so I put my water's ice cubes in it :( Dessert was watermelon and this condensed milk like brown sugar which was ehh. Our server was super friendly and attentive. Clean interior as well. I will try their a la carte menu next time!!

Best Indian in town!!!!!
I love Indian food and try out all the best restaurants! You won't be disappointed here! The vindaloo is especially amazing. Harry took great care of us! His service was fantastic!

I'd rate customer service 4stars- the guy was very welcoming and even explained to us what the different dishes were. But since I'm sure most of us are interested in how the food is-that's what I'll focus on. We did the buffet which was good but could be better. They had four vegetarian/vegan options which was great; however the paneer was incredibly spicy and salty. I would say though that the naan was perfect! I love the rice that Indian restaurants serve but since we were there an hour before the end of their buffet time, they came out with a different kind of white rice. Besides the salt factor, the food really wasn't bad. I've seen a few more options though at other places for buffet. The place does have a nice, unique setting though. Makes for a semi-romantic evening out but it also reminds me of a dance studio with the check out counter on a stage and the number of speakers.

I wanted to eat off the strip, partly to reign in the cost of a decent meal and partly to actually get a decent meal that was not ladened with fried foods. We had noticed the Jannat while running errands earlier in the day, and while we don't often partake of Indian food and actually know very little about it we very much enjoy it. 

It was clearly a family restaurant. The owner took our order, explaining what the various foods were and how they were prepared. We ordered the navratan (?) Korma and following their recommendation for a couple non-Indian palates also ordered the chicken Tonka masala. Both were lovely, delicately spiced and of the perfect quantity. 

Considering its proximity to the Worldmark we like to frequent, it will be a do over for us.

We don't eat Indian food much but would like to try other restaurants. This was our first here in Las Vegas and it was very good. Service was good, staff was friendly and restaurant was clean. We will go there again after we've tried other Indian restaurants to see how they compare.

Live really close to here and was excited to be getting an Indian restaurant close by. Went for the lunch buffet and it was really good! My gf and I were the only people in there so we got a lot of great service lol. Chicken in the chicken tikka was moist and not fatty, not spicy though I wouldn't have minded the extra spicy. Tried some other dishes I normally don't eat and everything I tried was really good! Got seconds... Then thirds. What's cooler is that they do have a dinner buffet too. Most places I've been the buffet is only for lunch. I'd go back for sure.

We decided to deviate from our favorite Indian restaurant and give Jannat Indian Cuisine a try and I am glad we did. It is now my new favorite. The waiter, Harry, was very friendly and attentive. Service with a smile. Sonny the owner made sure to greet us.  I really appreciate the personal touch that added.   Had chili paneer, butter chicken and my husband had goat saag.  All was Delicious!! We will certainly come back for more.
Holy moly... Hot and delicious.  Fresh well prepared well priced.  I was extremely satified, got level 3 hot....was really nicely spicey.  Leftover heaven.

Yay! A closer AYCE lunch buffet for me. The food was pretty good.  Chicken tikka masala was juicy and not as dry as everyone stated.  The sauce was a bit spicy, but flavorful and I got used to the spice. The tandoori chicken is one of the best in town, and I've been to more than a handful of AYCE Indian buffets. The rice was fresh and fluffy. The naan (I got plain,) was soft on the inside and crunchy on the outside.  The chicken curry was a bit dry (not crazy,) but the sauce was tasty. They had a couple veggie dishes and all were pretty good. I didn't see any samosas or spinach paneer, but that's not going to stop me from coming back.  
Even the gulag jamun was rich and delicious in a heavier sugar syrup.  
The owner kept checking up on me, I told him I preferred much saltier flavors, but I blame that on my pregnancy. 
All in all, it was around $17 for me and the buffet with a soda. I will be back with the hubbs one day.

First off, this establishment deserves 5 stars but they forgot my raita in the order that I had delivered so I unfortunately will have to give them four. Their delivery price is also 9 bucks which is steep but I was desperate for some good Indian without leaving my house. I'm kinda lazy.

But that's two negatives out of many positives.  I've been searching for a delicious Indian place ever since I moved here.  I found some good ones but not a great one like this.  I'm originally from New York and travelled overseas so I know good Indian food when I taste it.  This place is 100%  it.  The best in Vegas. 

I ordered the vegetable samosas, which in my opinion were huge. They came with 2 sauces, one was made with cilantro and the other could possibly be mango.  It was more on the sweeter side but not chunky like a chutney. My one samosa was a little too salty but the other one was just fine. I'll obviously let it slide. It was yummy.

I ordered the butter chicken and the chicken korma.  I honestly couldn't decide between the 2 so I figured I would just eat them both within a couple days for lunches and dinner.  I made them both medium spiced because I didn't know how spicy they can get.  The flavors in both were amazing.  I dipped the pants off my onion naan in both sauces.  They were perfectly done.  It reminded me of the restaurant I go to back home so I was delighted.

The naan was excellent too. Full of red onion. Nice and soft. I wish it was a little bit more crisp but that's what you get when you order delivery.
  
Overall if you are looking for awesome Indian fare, stop right here. Order. Do it.
Service was great! Buffet had variety and everything we tried was tasty. The ambience was nice too.
Maybe the chef just had a mediocre day? The food was bland, not spicy and for the first time ever I got heart burn. The naan is amazing but I'll stick with my other Indian cuisine.
Wonderful food, excellent service, I would highly recommend.  I have been out of NYC for a while, but the food was comparable to the best, if not better...

Whether you are a student homesick for Indian food or someone with a hankering for curry Jannat is the place for you. Half the credit goes to the food which is unabashedly Authentic food and the other goes to the owner Sunny who instantly welcomes you and showers you with some good old fashioned desi hospitality. 
 

We ordered Gobi Manchurian, Black Dal and Paneer Makhani ( not in the menu but made for my husband ) . It came piping hot with steamed rice and crisp Tandoori roti. 

We ended our meal with some hot chai and mental promises to ourselves to try the dal tadka and saag Channa next time

This place suffers since it's not on the main strip - but the food is spectacular and should be a definite destination you visit. Take it from a very fussy Indian cook herself.

This place is the best place for Indian food. Everything tastes so great. Especially for the lunch buffet, you can have high quality curry and bread with super low price. The light inside is kinda dark, that's the only thing I could complain. Beside that everything is perfect, the make fresh curry everyday and handmade their bread. I bring my friends here already, they love it.

I went there 3 times and will definetly go back when i feel like indian food because its tasty the owners are adorable and welcoming, a lot of hospitality, the service great, i mean yes they deserve 5* they are pretty new and i wish them to be there for a long time because they deserve it.and i am definetly one of their loyal customer!!
Enjoy!!

Perfection!  Indian done the way we like it.  We asked to have mild spices and our wish was granted. Chicken Saag, Chicken Korma and Aloo Gobi had all of the flavor without the excessive heat although I'm sure heat lovers can have it as spicy as desired.

A nice atmosphere inside, convenient location at Tropicana and Duneville and super friendly staff.  Has only been open a short time but is now our go-to for Indian and is sure to become popular.  Give it a try!

I ordered delivery since e it was a cold raining evening in Las Vegas.  it arrived on time as promised and hot. The tikka chicken was delicious, just the right amount of spice.  The nann was cooked great, nice and fluffy.  The only disappointment was the vegetable samosas. They were very heavy and greasy.   I can't wait to dine there in person.

Came here as I was in the area, since i was craving some curry. The food was okay. Side note there was no one there but me.... several customer walked in but then left. The Garlic naan was made freshly which was very delicious. The buffet lunch was not too bad. I only wish each dish was hotter. Overall it was okay. I give it a 3 star.

I am really thankful for this amazing meal and fabulous service. We were guided through the menu and were able to try an Indian dessert that was delicious. They have a lunchtime buffet that I really want to try. It's a cute little place with great food and they play music videos while you eat. It's a very cultural experience and I highly recommend eating here.

This restaurant has great food and friendly service. Food is fresh ... Awesome butter chicken and palak paneer. Buffet is reasonably priced.
I will go again for sure!

Very disappointing! We ordered food for take-away and it was totally not we accepted. The chicken tikka was chewy and tasteless. The lamb kebab had no flavor at all. Biryani was tasteless. Seemed like left overs from lunch buffet.

My first 2-star restaurant review... I really didn't want to write this, but for me, all the 4-5 star reviews were misleading.  Maybe their regular buffet cook called in sick or something because this was the first time that I didn't go for second helpings at a buffet.  I came in on a Friday for lunch around noon, and what I immediately noticed was how dark it was inside. There was only one person in before me, and I was disappointed to see that the buffet offerings were hardly much of anything compared to several other Indian restaurants I've tried. The goat meat was tough to chew, the tandoori chicken was dry, and the gulab jamun tasted like pasty, soggy cotton balls, ick.  The complimentary naan bread was average, but you only get buttered or plain whereas the higher end Indian buffets (like ahem, Mint Indian Bistro) generously include garlic naan made fresh to order.  At least the veggie curries were decent enough, but how can you mess up veggies simmered in curry sauce?  Thank goodness I know what better tasting Indian food tastes like, and I'll be returning to those buffets instead.

The place has a design and decorations that is good for parties. Club lights all over the ceiling and speakers all around a DJ in the center ..bar in a side .. so good food.. i feel home eating at that place as if you chef a mother cooking with love and care. Quality is A1.
Whoever is running that place is doing a great job.

The food was ok, not stellar in any way.

I was the only one there on a Tuesday at 7:30pm. I ordered Malai Kofta to compare it with the same dish offered by Mount Everest on W Sahara. Mount Everest seems consistently very good, but I wanted to try a different place. Jannat was: Wrong choice, it turned out.

The three mistakes:

1) I ordered it spicy, 8/10. It arrived at tourist spice, maybe a 3. 

2) Garlic naan had enough garlic, but was otherwise really bland. The rice, Jasmine long grain, tasted mealy, and was clumped in places.

3) The menu, which listed these as $11.95 and $2.95 respectively, did not make the price trip to the final bill, which overcharged each by a dollar. The waitress/cashier seemed indignant that I had brought this up, and I politely showed her the menu, and the bill. After a bit of reprogramming, the final bill reflected the *actual* price. 

The waitress/cashier would have found out about #1 if she had ever visited the table after the order was taken, but it wasn't until late in the meal that she sauntered over.

The ambience is: converted Mexican Cantina. I expected at least normal, but they failed that test, and their customer service attitude was bizarre at best, insulting at worst.

I won't be back.
This is my favorite Indian restaurant and it's close to home. The food is always hot and delicious. The service is equally good. I recommend this place if you want a great Indian lunch or dinner.
Jannat was very good. I really enjoyed my meal there. The naan bread was fantastic, and I liked the atmosphere of the restaurant. The staff was incredible, very kind and prompt. Thank you!!
Really good Indian spot! Best Indian food I've had in a long time. Definitely recommend it.
Great food and great service. We came for the lunch buffet and liked the vibe. Dessert at the end was good too.

Wasn't excellent. Indian fare buffets always appeal to me - and being in Vegas I guess my standards were too high. Dry, chewy chicken. Tandoori tasted like freezer burn. The butter chicken was actually hardboil eggs in sauce. Rice was incredibly dry and hard. Wasn't busy at all, myself and another table. Two tables sat dirty the entire course of my meal. At one point the server refilled my water while having a conversation on her cellphone. My naan arrived at the end of my rough meal. Will pass.

The food tastes good, don't get me wrong, but do NOT order delivery. The portions were ridiculously small. Like lunch portions, for dinner. And for that size the price is crazy. So, 5/5 for taste and speed of delivery. 2/5 for portion size and cost. If I eat here again it won't be take-out.

Thank you to the staff & owners of Jannat for making yet another visit a wonderful dining experience!  From your garlic nan to lamb masala, chana masala, goat curry, chicken curry, tandoori chicken & butter chicken your food continues to have the quality & consistency of the top Indian cuisine in town.  For those nearby during lunch, don't forget to check out their great lunch buffet at a terrific value!  For this visit, I was able to introduce a friend who's never had Indian food before & he loved it!

We were visiting from Utah, and decided to take a chance on the lunch buffet at Jannat. We were not disappointed, In fact we went back for dinner the same day. Very friendly service, and great food. Loved the saag paneer, and chicken tikka masalla. We'll be back next time we're in town.

My wife and i went as we wanted to see if it was any good. Risky as Indian food in Las Vegas can be hit or miss.

The food was excellent, I had the Lamb Vindaloo and I would say it was one of the best I've had in town. The other dishes were delightful and we left with leftovers, which is always good.

Service was excellent, our server Harry was flawless.

This is a new place and deserves to be successful, if you like Indian food, give it try. You won't be disappointed.

I have experienced good Indian good and mediocre Indian good. I can honestly say Jannat is some of the best Indian food I have ever had. The palak paneer was fresh and the paneer was soft and moist. The butter naan was freshly baked and warm. 

The service was attentive and friendly. I would highly recommend them for dining in or take out.
Love the food ! So good. Pricing was a bit high I'm assuming to meet the overhead of the large eating area inside . Food was delish, chicken Tiki Masala so good

I got delivery on Grubhub. I ordered the butter chicken, rice, and garlic naan for $35. The rice was jasmine instead of basmati which I thought was a little odd. The curry was really thin and watery but super orange, my mouth was stained after eating it. It had ok flavor but somewhat sour. The chicken was cut into thin strips which I'm also not used to, normally it would be chunks of chicken. The naan tasted really good but was still doughy. I ate about 1/4 of everything so it wouldnt go to waste and I would have something to eat for dinner. I won't be eating the leftovers or ordering from here again.
I love coming here for lunch. The food is great and the owner is super nice. I would truly recommend trying this place out!

Just ordered take out (saag paneer and chicken tikka masala) .... And I have to say I've found my new favorite spot for Indian food in Vegas. Layers of flavor, tender chicken, and a huge serving of basmati rice. Yum!  I'll be back!!

I was thoroughly impressed with this great lunch deal. 

I have just returned from Birmingham UK, and the Indian food over there is a dime a dozen of greatness. However, upon my return, I have been itching for some Indian food. Most places I do no not mind spending a little extra, but for lunch, I just wanted a taste. 

Jannat Indian Cuisine offers that and more in their lunch deal. You can not beat it. The best part, it is really delicious. They did a great job bringing authenticity to las vegas with both a meat and veggie option. Tops!!

Thank you for the great lunch, we will be returning!

Wow- ordered chilli chicken and Gobi manchurian. Massive quantity of appetizer which is exactly what I want. Really please with that and the lady who owns the place came out and gave us a big intro to the whole restaurant. Thanks for the awesome dinner lavanya!

The buffet is $9.99 + tax. I love Indian food so I decided to try this place out! It was pretty good. The reason I am giving them 4 starts is because there wasn't a huge variety of food. The customer service was just ok, nothing overly amazing. The only complain I have is that the Naan bread was not baked/cooked all the way. I was able to pull parts of the bread apart just like melted cheese. All in all this was an ok restaurant. The food was ok as well as the customer service. Nothing horribly bad, nothing amazing.

This place is fairly new and a little further away from the Strip but i would definitely say it's worth the drive.We went in for dinner and were warmly greeted by the staff,after settling down at the booth the complimentary papadum was served with two varieties of chutney tamarind and mint.

We then placed our order
~Sweet Lassi $3.95
~Chilli chicken (spicy) $12.95
~chicken and egg fried rice $5.95

The lassi was perfect and the fried rice and chilli chicken were good.
What i noticed instantly  was the portions,they were way more generous than the average indian restaurants for the price point.Then the owner walked up to our table and asked us if we liked the Food,now me being a snob for indian food i was ready with various points and we got talking about how much we missed the taste of authentic Indian street food/dhabas.
He said they could totally customise it if we specify before ordering.

so I decided to get some food to-go
~Butter chicken $14.95
~Tandoori chicken $12.95
 
All the curries are served with a side of Rice.

I was blown away by the Tandoori chicken as was my husband and transported directly back to India.The chicken was well marinated,juicy and succulent with the right amount of spice.
The gravy of the butter chicken is one of the best i have had in the US.

We were so happy that we got the tandoori chicken and Cheese Naan to-go the very next day.
And Again it turned out to be perfect (this tandoori chicken is definitely a 5 in my books).

They also have a buffet for lunch which i'm going to try when i'm in town again.
The management is friendly and courteous,they will make you feel very Welcome.

Cheers!

I'm not a fan of writing bad reviews... but this food was bland. Bland, bland, bland. We are fans of Indian food, and yet this was just very disappointing given how well rated this place is. The chicken was obviously reheated several times as it was VERY tough. The sauce and spices seemed to all be "watered down". Not sure if this was on purpose. 

We had Chicken Tikka Masala and Chili Chicken. The chicken in both was REALLY tough and dry. Vegetable Breyani rice was tasteless.

This is what I call, Indian food well made and well served. I tried the paneer tikka and Chana saag both were really well made. I am going to go here again soon to try out Delhi style street food :)

Also dont forget to ask for the chapati (tawa roti)

This is a wonderful place to go. When you increase the heat on a scale of 1-10, you don't lose flavor for heat. The service is very friendly, and they have chili Naan and butter Naan. I had the butter chicken, which is one of my favorite dishes, and I am picky about what it takes to be good. It is wonderful here, and my dad's chicken vindaloo was great. Their mango ice cream dessert is a perfect end to a flavor filled experience. I would give ten stars if I could!

Open for thanksgiving and they are in the process of also bringing the Indian sandwich to Las Vegas which is exciting news because no other restaurant here in town offers that.

They have a good assortment of vegetarian dishes in their lunch buffet and I highly recommend the lunch buffet for anyone who loves Indian food but also to vegetarians.  For vegans they will make you a special dish omitting butter as you prefer.
This place was freaking fantastic. Perfect seasoning and great atmosphere. I highly recommend this place to everyone. Im a foodie too so I critique everthing.

In Las Vegas on business and love Indian food. Ate here this evening and truly enjoyed the entire experience. Especially friendly and helpful with any menu questions and more. Loved our cauliflower appetizer, and our butter chicken and paneer sauce dinners along with the hot marsala tea. Thank you Jannat Indian Cuisine for a wonderful dinner and dining experience. Love the open ceiling and friendly family atmosphere. A wonderful and lucky choice for us. We'll be back! Thank you friends!
Went tonight for anniversary dinner. Sign on door day's call for lease information. Appears to be out of business

Went in for the lunch buffet, not sure whether it was the timing off the day but every item I tried was very acidic/sour.  Curries should be savoury and rich not bland.  A slight suggestion please visit your competitions like India Masala Bar and grill, you might be able to pick up a few ideas.  I'm all for any Indian restaurants succeeding here in the Valley, so hopefully this review is an opportunity for you to improve.  Thank You.
We LOVED the whole experience!! The food was soo delicious and the prices are soo  great. They have the best customer service and we highly recommend this great Indian Cuisine restaurant.

New place with few patrons on a Tuesday evening. However, the family is extremely warm, friendly, and welcoming. They were very patient to explain the items on the menu and asking us how each dish tasted. This place offers very delicious Indian dishes. You can find all the classics. Highly recommend lamb korma and papdi chat.

Stopped here for dinner the other night, and it was EXCELLENT.

I had Chicken Tikki Masala, and it was exactly like I like it.  The appetizers were good, the ambience is very cool.  If you go at night, they play Indian music videos for you, which were super fun. 


All in all I highly recommend, and I will be back.

If you know Indian food, you know how hard it is to get an amazing dish, we'll this new place has the goods! The malai kofta has decent sized balls, the tikki masalas chicken was amazing, tender and full of flavor, the vindaloo has a great hearty flavor and the garlic naan i should have gotten more of, because my kids ate it all before i could get any! Portions are good,  the staff is friendly  (and not in that fake smile way, they are genuinely friendly) and I will be back for sure. Thanks guys for an amazing dinner!
Amazing food, big dishes and friendly smiling servers - what else I could ask for casual dinner. Thanks a lot!
the food had no flavor everything needed salt,the sign says Buffett opens at 11am had to wait 15minutes for them to set up!!! will not go back

Been wanting to try this place since it opened right down the street, and we were not disappointed! We went for the lunch buffet. It was very small in comparison to other Indian buffets (mt. Everest and ghandi) but what it lacked in choices, it certainly made up for with flavor and quality. Chicken Tika and chicken curry, a lentil dish, a paneer in red type curry dish, and goat curry were all fantastic. Tandoori chicken looked dry, but it wasn't, and was great. Mint chutney very refreshing. Garlic butter Naan was out of this world. I was really missing the fried veggie fritters and samosas and my ultimate fave-the spinach paneer dish. I'm sure all of that can be ordered a la carte though! Service was great and everyone was so friendly. Will be back to try again from the menu next time!

Worst restaurant ever..the buffet was absolutely disgusting...I never had to leave a restaurant because the food was that bad and go to another restaurant....every item in the lunch buffet tasted terrible nothing like how Indian food should taste...they tasted sour,stale. Probably old food from the previous day...I just don't understand how they can sell that food to people. I wouldn't be surprised if they ran out of business if they keep this up.

We went for lunch buffet. There was only one table of two people occupied and the time was2.0pmwe sat down and there was not much choice .lots of potato dishes.the butter chicken was  good.dal makhani was too dry.the first naan bread came fast but we asked for another one and waited forever to get one.the lady was busy on the phone and the owner was entertaining his friends.if this is the service they provide to the only table occupied then I am sure their restaurant will be a big success

We used Yelp24 to order Chicken Curry, Chicken Saag, Butter Naan, Chicken Tikka Masala, Vegetable Biryani, Gobhi Parantha. 

What I liked: 

1. Um guys, this place is SO GOOD. Special props to the Chicken Saag (wished however that I got mango chutney to go with it). 
2. Delivery was fast and everything was well packed. I like it when they cling wrap everything, so it was neat when we got it. 

What can be improved:

1. The portions were, I will say, a bit small for the price, but it really made it up with flavor. 

Got it for everyone at office, it was a hit. Go now!

Tried this restaurant few days ago. Liked there chicken tikka.... Biryani was awesome.... Chicken 
Palak was excellent. Will definitely go back.
Chicken was hard as a rock and naan had unpleasant texture. Very disappointed.
